{
  "answer": "**Mirza Ghalib's famous matla** (the opening couplet of his ghazal, Ghazal #204 in the *Diwan-e-Ghalib*) reads as follows:\n\n**Original (Urdu):**\n\n> یہ نہ تھی ہماری قسمت کہ وصال_یار ہوتا  \n> اگر اور جیتے رہتے یہی انتظار ہوتا[^1]\n\n**Transliteration (Roman Urdu):**\n\n> Yeh na thi hamari qismat ke visaal-e-yaar hota  \n> Agar aur jeete rehte yahi intezaar hota[^2]\n\n**Translation (English):**\n\n> To be with my Beloved was not my fate;  \n> Had I lived longer, waiting was my state.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/original/#p-0ed9be/).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/transliteration/#p-007848/).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/translation/#p-e43078/).",
